    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1281"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1281">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/55.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 20, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Petroleum Company has permission to resume operations until Monday night pending
                    conclusion of negotiations. General Aguilar sent telegraphic reply to my letter
                    and is following same with full reply by mail. States that they have given and
                    will give guarantees to foreign companies. I have advised companies not to pay
                    any of war tax demands. Necessary remain neutral but in last resort managers
                    these companies may be compelled to pay sums demanded in preference to having
                    valuable wells and storage destroyed. Respectfully request specific instructions
                    on this point for benefit of companies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
